            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To Arrenia Felicissima, sacerdos of [Mamaea?], [mother?] of the Augusti, daughter of Lucius Arrenius Menander. The college of youths (set this up) on account of her merits. This place was given by decree of the decurions.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Arrenia's father (Lucius Arrenius Menander) and mother (Bruttia L.f. Nereis) are elsewhere attested in Herdoniae. There are two options for the restoration of the dedicatee of Arrenia's priesthood: [[[Mamaeae | matris]]] Aug(usti) or [[[Iuliae | Mamaeae]]] Aug(ustae).</p> 
            </div>
